flowchart LR
    U[Unknown interval U] --> ABS[Absolute uncertainty Var(U)]
    ABS --> INCABS[Var(U) may remain or increase]

    K[Known interval K] --> TOTAL[Expected elapsed time E[tau]]
    U --> TOTAL
    R[Re-anchored known interval R] --> TOTAL

    INCABS --> SCALE[Uncertainty scale sqrt(Var(U))]
    TOTAL --> REF[Reference scale E[tau]]

    SCALE --> RATIO["rho(R) = sqrt(Var(U)) / E[tau]"]
    REF --> RATIO

    R --> INCREF[As R increases, E[tau] increases]
    INCREF --> COND[If reference scale grows faster than uncertainty scale]
    SCALE --> COND
    COND --> DILUTE[Relative uncertainty rho decreases]

    DILUTE --> CLAIM[Absolute uncertainty may grow while relative influence decreases]

    U:::unknown
    R:::known
    K:::known
    INCABS:::warn
    DILUTE:::good

    classDef unknown fill:#fff3e0,stroke:#ef6c00,stroke-width:1px;
    classDef known fill:#e8f5e9,stroke:#2e7d32,stroke-width:1px;
    classDef warn fill:#fff8e1,stroke:#f9a825,stroke-width:1px;
    classDef good fill:#e3f2fd,stroke:#1565c0,stroke-width:1px;
